content:
NewsGuard evaluated that DeepSeek's chatbot was only 17% accurate in providing news and information, ranking 10th out of 11 models including ChatGPT and Gemini.
According to a report released by NewsGuard, a media credibility rating service, on Wednesday, DeepSeek's chatbot repeated false claims 30% of the time and gave vague or useless answers 53% of the time when answering news-related prompts, resulting in a failure rate of 83%. Other robots had an average failure rate of 62% in this evaluation.
NewsGuard said it used the same 300 prompts for DeepSeek as it evaluates its Western counterparts, including 30 prompts based on 10 false claims spread online.

January 28, Yunnan. A man posted a video saying that he sold a watch, but was told that the money he received was fraudulent funds, which caused his bank card, WeChat and Alipay to be frozen and unusable. He called and sent messages to the police many times, but received no response.
The man said that in order to prove his innocence, he wanted the buyer to come to the police station to make a statement, but the police said that as long as he could prove that he was just selling the watch, there was no need to ask the buyer to come to make a statement.
Later, the police said that the watch was lost and might have flowed out of the country. They asked him if he was willing to return the fraudulent funds. The man refused and questioned the police's perfunctory attitude and failed his expectations.

fullContent:
一架美国客机星期三(1月29日)晚间在接近华盛顿里根国家机场时，与一架美国陆军的黑鹰直升机发生空中相撞，飞机坠毁在波托马克河，大量救难人员投入搜救行动。《哥伦比亚广播公司》(CBS)报道，截至美东时间晚上11点30分，至少已找到18具尸体。
 美国航空(American Airlines)发布声明，美鹰航空(American Eagle)5342航班从堪萨斯的威奇托(Wichita, Kansas)飞往华盛顿，该航班由太平洋西南航空(Pacific Southwest Airlines，PSA)的庞巴迪CRJ700支线客机执飞。确认该商用客机载有60名乘客和4名机组人员。
 美国军方证实黑鹰直升机上有3名军人，目前尚无两架飞机伤亡情况的详细信息。

content:
January 29 (Released) Shandong. The man said that his mother had an abscess on her waist. After the operation at the Second Affiliated Hospital of Shandong Medical University, on January 15, the department director suggested that his mother be transferred to the ICU for treatment, which would cost thousands of yuan a day. In order to give his mother better treatment conditions, the man agreed.
Later, the man wanted to visit his mother in the ICU but was rejected by the hospital. He did not see his mother until January 21. His mother told him that she was abused by medical staff, saying that she could only drink cold water every day, and could not even drink hot soup, and was tied to the bed.
The man said that he asked other tertiary hospitals and they all said that his mother's condition did not need to be admitted to the ICU. At present, the man has transferred his mother to other hospitals for treatment.

Howard Lutnick, the nominee for U.S. Secretary of Commerce, criticized Chinese artificial intelligence startup DeepSeek for stealing American technology and vowed to impose the highest tariffs on China.
At his confirmation hearing, Lutnick criticized DeepSeek for stealing American technology and creating "dirt cheap" artificial intelligence models.
He said bluntly, "They stole. They broke in. They stole our intellectual property. This must end. I will strictly enforce restrictions and ensure that these restrictions are enforced to maintain our leading position, because we must stay ahead."
Lutnick also said that DeepSeek circumvented U.S. export controls and purchased a large number of Nvidia chips. "This can't go on. If they want to compete with us, let them come, but don't use our tools to compete with us. I am on this point...
fullContent:
美国商务部长提名人选卢特尼克（Howard Lutnick）批评中国人工智能初创公司深度求索（DeepSeek）盗取美国技术，更誓言要对中国征收最高关税。
 特尼克在提名确认听证会上批评深度求索盗取美国技术，创建“超廉价”（dirt cheap）的人工智能模型。
 他直言，“他们偷了东西。他们闯了进来。他们窃取了我们的知识产权。这必须结束，我将严格执行限制措施，并确保这些限制得到执行，以保持我们的领先地位，因为我们必须保持领先”。
 卢特尼克还说，深度求索规避了美国的出口管制，采购大量英伟达的晶片。“不能再这样下去，如果他们要和我们竞争，那就放马过来，但别用我们的工具来跟我们竞争。我在这一点上会表现得非常强硬”。

content: Cambodian media reported that Cambodian police cracked a Chinese kidnapping gang, rescued 1 Chinese woman and arrested 2 suspects. After investigation, the police launched a raid in a residential area in Langkor District, Phnom Penh on the 26th. The police successfully rescued a 40-year-old Chinese woman Zhao Kangli (transliteration) and arrested two Chinese suspects on the spot, namely 27-year-old Jiao Youke (transliteration) and 37-year-old Zheng Naiwen (transliteration). The police report said that the two suspects confessed that their criminal gang had a total of 3 people, who specifically kidnapped Chinese and Vietnamese women, forced them into suitcases and extorted ransoms. So far, the gang has committed 6 crimes. At present, the police have handed over the two suspects to the prosecutor of the Phnom Penh Primary Court for handling in accordance with the law.

Failure to meet the requirements will result in punishment, which has caused panic among the people. Trump to cancel student visas for all "Hamas sympathizers," White House officials say.
Trump signed an executive order on Wednesday to combat anti-Semitism, saying he would use "all available and appropriate legal tools" to prosecute and deport perpetrators of "illegal anti-Semitic harassment and violence," White House officials said.
"To all foreign residents who engage in pro-jihadist protests, we issue a warning: By 2025, we will find you and deport you," Trump said in the fact sheet. "I will also swiftly cancel student visas for Hamas sympathizers on all college campuses, which have been overrun by radicalism as never before."
